A '''cock and bull story''' is a far fetched and fanciful [[story]] or [[tale]].

==English==

===Etymology===
The term is believed to have originated from [[wikipedia:stage coach]] travellers' gossip and rumour exchanged between two [[wikipedia:coaching inns]], ''The Cock'' and ''The Bull'' in [[wikipedia:Stony Stratford]].  These inns were a main stopping point on the [[wikipedia:turnpike]] road from [[wikipedia:London]] to [[wikipedia:Birmingham]], [[wikipedia:Chester]] and [[wikipedia:North Wales]] (for [[wikipedia:Ireland]]).

